articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mahmoud Issa, Dawoud Abu Alkas
articles.description: Many of the hundreds of thousands of Palestinians expected to head back to the northern Gaza Strip will return to homes in ruins.
articles.title: Gazans ready tent camps for families returning to north after ceasefire

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Moscow Mayor Sergei Sobyanin said early on Friday that air defence units had intercepted attacks by Ukrainian drones at four locations around the Russian capital.
articles.title: Moscow mayor says air defences repel Ukrainian drone attacks aimed at capital

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The deployment of the U.S. military's Typhon missile launchers in the Philippines was in line with Washington's longstanding defence ties with the country, the Philippine armed forces said on Friday.
articles.title: Philippine military says US missile deployment to boost readiness, support regional security

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres has warned that eastern Congo's M23 conflict risks spiralling into a broader regional war, his spokesperson said in a statement, condemning the rebels' capture of another strategic town, Sake.
articles.title: UN warns Congo's M23 conflict could spark regional war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hungary wants the European Union to persuade Ukraine to resume gas transit from Russia to Europe, Prime Minister Viktor Orban said on Friday, signalling a tough debate as the EU seeks to extend its sanctions against Russia over the coming week.
articles.title: Hungary wants Ukraine gas transit to resume as EU sanctions rollover looms

articles.author: Emma Farge, Jennifer Rigby
articles.description: The World Health Organization will cut costs and review which health programmes to prioritise after President Donald Trumpannounced he was withdrawing the U.S. from the agency, the WHO's chief told staff in an internal memo seen by Reuters.
articles.title: WHO chief to cut costs, reset priorities after US exit, document shows

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A first round of wage talks for more than 2.5 million public sector employees in Germany kicked off outside Berlin on Friday.
articles.title: German public sector employees kick off wage negotiations

articles.author: Sam Tobin, Michael Holden
articles.description: A British teenager who killed three young girls at a Taylor Swift-themed dance event was jailed for at least 52 years on Thursday, for an attack Prime Minister Keir Starmer called one of the most harrowing moments in Britain's history.
articles.title: UK teenager jailed for minimum of 52 years for 'harrowing' Southport girls' murders

articles.author: Isabelle Carlsson, Tom Little
articles.description: The creator of the Danish political TV drama "Borgen", Adam Price, says U.S. President Donald Trump's wish to control Greenland has created an "absurd" reality that has made it more challenging to write political fiction.
articles.title: 'Borgen' creator says fiction challenged by Trump's Greenland gambit

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Maltese court on Friday granted bail to a prominent businessman who is charged with complicity in the murder of anti-corruption journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia in 2017.
articles.title: Businessman charged over Malta journalist's murder granted bail
